      "rationale": "Acceptance criteria defined prior to comparison: percent difference <10% and E/uval <1.96 for each QoI. All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) meet both criteria. E/uval values: stiffness 0.81, yield force 1.34, force at 40 mm 1.12."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. All three QoIs directly reflect the construct's ability to withstand physiological compression-bending loads without permanent deformation."
    },
    {
